# Pinned versions and SHA-256 sums for the DNS bundle, embedded in the
# awg-easy-rs binary. build.rs reads this file and validates that the
# vendored .gz blobs match the expected SHAs at compile time.
#
# Each binary is recorded as:
#   <NAME>_VERSION   = <upstream tag / version string>
#   <NAME>_AMD64_SHA256 = <SHA-256 of the *uncompressed* ELF, lowercase hex>
#
# x86_64 (amd64) is the only supported target — see
# vendor/README.md → "Supported architectures" for the rationale.
#
# The runtime extractor (src/dns/runtime.rs) hashes the on-disk ELF and
# skips re-extraction when it already matches — same pattern as the
# Xray bundle. Bumping a binary means: download upstream → SHA-verify
# the upstream archive → extract → `gzip -9 -c` into vendor/ → update
# the version string and the AMD64 SHA here.
#
# Until the blobs land in vendor/, all SHAs are blank. build.rs treats
# blank SHAs as "this binary is not bundled" and refuses to enable the
# `dns_bundled` cfg gate, so builds keep working with no DNS-bundle
# support until the curation step is done.

